Originally, I also wanted to do like that, but I noticed that:

int osd_xattr_get(const struct lu_env *env, struct dt_object *dt,
                  struct lu_buf *buf, const char *name)
{
...
                rc = osd_xattr_get_internal(env, obj, buf, name, &size);
        up_read(&obj->oo_guard);

        if (rc == -ENOENT)
                rc = -ENODATA;
...
}

It means that for osd-zfs, the caller of osd_xattr_get() cannot distinguish whether it is the target object destroyed or the EA absence from the the returned errno "-ENODATA". It is your old patch, I am not certain for that that. So I choose another safe way of checking the object destroyed or not by the caller directly.

